Full Article Fetch Test - MANGALAM
================================================================================

Net Profit (TTM/latest) (2025-10-19): -137983000.00

Title   : Mangalam Worldwide Q2 net profit jump 52% 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-19T03:34:25
Fetched : 2025-10-19T19:46:39.719545
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/mangalam-worldwide-q2-net-profit-jump-52/article70181702.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Stainless-steel manufacturer Mangalam Worldwide has reported a 52 per cent year-on-year rise in consolidated net profit at ₹10.53 crore for the quarter ended September 30, supported by higher revenues.
It had posted a net profit of ₹6.91 crore in the same quarter last year, the company said in an exchange filing on Friday.
Its total income for the reporting quarter rose 33 per cent to ₹318.52 crore from ₹239.48 crore recorded last year.
Adjusted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation (adjusted EBITDA) stood at ₹21.50 crore, up 59 per cent from ₹13.48 crore in the year-ago period.
"We continue to focus on developing value-added products that enhance our operating margins and strengthen profitability," Chandragupt Prakash Mangal, Managing Director of Mangalam Worldwide, said.
Ahmedabad-based Mangalam Worldwide is an integrated stainless steel player with an annual capacity of 1,80,000 metric tonnes.
The company recently transitioned from SME platform to mainboard on National Stock Exchange.
Published on October 19, 2025

